  "texts": [
    "However, they are limited for the following three reasons.",
    "First, their empirical results are not sufficient enough as their training and evaluation datasets are relatively limited (e.g., Shepherd [58] is based on 1 training and 1 evaluation dataset).",
    "Second, none of them consider value alignment, which is a critical last step before launching contemporary Chatbots [3].",
    "Third, both of them are limited to FedAvg [20] as the only FL method, while neglecting the diverse FL algorithms that have been shown to perform better depending on the tasks.Unlike previous works, in this paper, we provide the most comprehensive exploration on FL and contemporary LLMs to date.",
    "From the perspective of LLMs, we explore both of the two critical steps in the current LLMs training paradigm, including instruction tuning and value alignment."
  ],
